  "description": "Rare Good Condition Kelly 28 \u2013 Natural Epsom (Old Courchevel)\nThis Kelly 28 is crafted from Old Courchevel, a type of cowhide leather that was discontinued in 2000. In 2004, its successor became known as Grand Epsom. This leather is highly prized for its durability, refined texture, and structured appearance. It is most commonly used in Kelly Sellier models, where the exterior stitching enhances the bag\u2019s luxurious, elegant look while making it stronger than many other leathers.\n\t\u2022\tHardware: Gold (GHW)\n\t\u2022\tStamp: Z in a circle (1996)\n\t\u2022\tDetails: Original, neat, and elegant Sellier stitching. The only distinction lies in the strap hook. While it cannot be compared to current models in terms of price, its quality remains timeless and of international standard.\n\nComes with: Herm\u00e8s box, Herm\u00e8s dust bag, strap, key set, and authentication card from Vestiaire.\n\nNote: This beloved vintage piece has been professionally retouched including a handle replacement by Herm\u00e8s. A copy of the Herm\u00e8s receipt is included.\n\nThis bag has been authenticated by Vestiaire.\n",
